%N A393903 Numbers k such that the digit reversals of k, when written in all bases 2 to 10, are greater than k.
%H A393903 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A393903/b393903.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A393903 143 is a term as 143 = 143_10 = 168_9 = 217_8 = 263_7 = 355_6 = 1033_5 = 2033_4 = 12022_3 = 10001111_2 whose digital reversals are 341_10 = 341, 861_9 = 703, 712_8 = 458, 362_7 = 191, 553_6 = 213, 3301_5 = 451, 3302_4 = 242, 22021_3 = 223, 11110001_2 = 241, all of which are greater than 143.
%t A393903 q[k_]:=AllTrue[IntegerReverse[k,Range[2,10]],#>k&];Select[Range[4787],q] (* _James C. McMahon_, Mar 02 2026 *)
